<topic id='business_definition_cancer_treatment_period.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Cancer Treatment Period - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_cancer_treatment_period">Cancer Treatment Period</xref>
 is an 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_activity_group">ACTIVITY GROUP</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_cancer_treatment_period">Cancer Treatment Period</xref>
 is:        </p>
      <ul>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
initiated when a 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_decision_to_treat">Decision To Treat</xref>
 for a cancer condition is made and                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
ends when the 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 receives the 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_planned_cancer_treatment">Planned Cancer Treatment</xref>
 specified in the 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_cancer_care_plan">Cancer Care Plan</xref>
 covering the 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
 condition. This is the same as 
                                <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_treatment_start_date__cancer_">TREATMENT START DATE (CANCER)</xref>.                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
The full list of 
              <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
               keyref="supporting_definition_international_classification_of_diseases__icd_">International Classification of Diseases (ICD)</xref>
 diagnosis codes is available on the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nhs_digital">NHS Digital</xref>
 website at: 
              <xref href="https://digital.nhs.uk/cancer-waiting-times"
               scope="external"
               format="html">Cancer Waiting Times</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
If the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 receives several different types of treatment within the same 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_cancer_care_plan">Cancer Care Plan</xref>
 (e.g. surgery, followed by 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_chemotherapy">Chemotherapy</xref>, followed by 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_radiotherapy">Radiotherapy</xref>), then each stage has its own 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_cancer_treatment_period">Cancer Treatment Period</xref>
 of 31 days between 
              <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_decision_to_treat_date">DECISION TO TREAT DATE</xref>
 (or 
              <xref outputclass="element"
               keyref="element_earliest_clinically_appropriate_date">EARLIEST CLINICALLY APPROPRIATE DATE</xref>) and 
              <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_treatment_start_date__cancer_">TREATMENT START DATE (CANCER)</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_cancer_care_setting__treatment_">CANCER CARE SETTING (TREATMENT)</xref>
 is used to derive whether a waiting time adjustment between 
              <xref outputclass="element"
               keyref="element_cancer_treatment_period_start_date">CANCER TREATMENT PERIOD START DATE</xref>
 and 
              <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_treatment_start_date__cancer_">TREATMENT START DATE (CANCER)</xref>
 may be recorded in 
              <xref outputclass="element"
               keyref="element_waiting_time_adjustment__treatment_">WAITING TIME ADJUSTMENT (TREATMENT)</xref>.        </p>
  </div>
